        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10995",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Eugene is working on fixing the mysqli adapter that is in the incubator\/ folder.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-17T21:41:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-17T21:41:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11001",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What file version do you use?\n\n{code}\n\/**\n     * Prepare a statement and return a PDOStatement-like object.\n     *\n     * @param  string  $sql  SQL query\n     * @return Zend_Db_Statment|PDOStatement\n     *\/\n    public function prepare($sql) {\n    \t\n    \t$this->_connect();\n        return $this->_connection->prepare($sql);\n    \t\n    }\n{code}\n\nIn it's turn $this->_connection is\n\n{code}\n$this->_connection =& new mysqli($this->_config['host'], $this->_config['username'], $this->_config['password'], $this->_config['dbname']);\n{code}\n\nSo the prepare method should return prepared mysqli statement per\nhttp:\/\/ru2.php.net\/manual\/en\/function.mysqli-prepare.php",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-18T10:19:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-18T10:19:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11028",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "i use the svn version 3 weekd ago, i do not know the revison number, because i exported it. the creation date of the file is 03.10.2006 - 00:46 and size is 8.764kb\n\nthe prepare method works, but what i mean is that it is not consitencewith the rest of the statments.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-21T18:27:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-21T18:27:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11029",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I tried to make it compatible with all other adapters. \nmysqli_statement do not have all requiered methods and I use mysqli_result sometimes in the code. Finally it works I believe.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-22T04:11:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-22T04:11:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11030",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "where can i get the changed files?!?\n\ni searched in the svn but could not find it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-22T04:52:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-22T04:52:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11031",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "hmm i looked up in the code and found that many things are missing\nfor example in the abstract class Zend_Db_Statement there is no property $this->_connection, but is used in class\n\nmissing : protected $_connection = null;\n\nin the class Zend_Db_Statement_Mysqli the method execute refers to a property that does not exist  $this->_db line #104\n\nshould be $this->_connection->getConnection()\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chicodichery",
                        "name": "chicodichery",
                        "displayName": "Saqib Javed",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-22T06:03:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-22T06:03:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11036",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What are you talking about?\n\nZend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli herits from Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract. Line 71:     \n{code}protected $_connection = null;{code}\nThen, see Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli.php, line 275\n\n{code}$this->_connection =& new mysqli($this->_config['host'], $this->_config['username'], $this->_config['password'], $this->_config['dbname']);{code}\n\n\n\nZend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli has nothing to do with Zend_Db_Statement_Mysqli. I tried to adapt Zend_Db_Statement_Mysqli, but there were too much methods mysqli_stmt does not have. Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli works directly with mysqli_stmt. I will change it in future versions, a bit later.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eugenep",
                        "name": "eugenep",
                        "displayName": "Eugene Panaitov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-22T15:37:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-22T15:37:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11052",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Saqib, please update to the latest version of SVN.  Normally, we only address bugs in the most current version of the framework, since we are still working on preview releases of the ZF.  Please follow the instructions below to update to the most current code (and most current version of the mysqli adapter in the incubator directory):\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV\/Zend+Framework+Subversion+Standards",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
